rComments: She is a very good prof, however, I did not find that I learned much in class - learning was very independent and she really emphasized what was important to go over on your own, during class time. The exams were very fair, just read the textbook!! Labs were overwhelming, however, very useful and she was incredibly helpful in the lab!

She's a great prof- knows her stuff and always has interesting stories to tell from her own experiences in the field! You really need to be an independent studier though because there's a ton more that you have to know than what is discussed in class. Very fair with marks. The final was a pain because of the amount of information! Buy the textbook!

Class is relatively easy but she skips tons of slides/gives info to learn that is not in slides. Not a big deal if you have the text. Because of this the lecture is essentially useless. In labs she sits on her computer while we practice techniques, unsure if we are doing them right or not. Always short and condescending when you ask questions.

Nice prof. She definitely knows the topic well. Her labs are super interesting and useful, and it is easy to get a good grade in the labs. In class, she often would skip 10 slides and just say "you're responsible to know that". Her final exam was straightforward, but you need to learn most of the material yourself.
Extremely good prof, very very knowledgeable due to her extensive experience. Also a very understanding and likeable prof.
